                  SchemaManager schemaManager,
                  boolean isReplicaOp)
           throws ScimException,
                  SchemaException
        Used to create a request context that exists within a single SCIM Bulk operation
        Parameters:
        bulkReqOp - A parsed JSON structure representing a single SCIM bulk operation
        schemaManager - A pointer to the server ConfigMgr object (for schema)
        isReplicaOp - A flag indicating if request is from a replication event
        Throws:
        SchemaException - thrown when the bulk request JSON structure is invalid
        ScimException - thrown due to a schema or other Scim related issue

                  SchemaManager schemaManager)
           throws ScimException
        Constructor typically used in Spring Web Controller using annotated values from mapping, requestparam and requestheader annotations.
        Parameters:
        sctx - The ServletContext handling the request (@ServletContext). Used mainly for getRealPath
        resType - A String containing the top level container or resource type path element
        id - A String that is the resource identifier (typically a GUID).
        allParams - All parameters after "?" e.g. as provided by @RequestParam Map allParams
        allHeaders - All HTTP request headers e,g, as provided by @RequestHeader MultiValueMap headers
        body - Optional, the request body (e.g. from PATCH or PUT)
        schemaManager - A pointer to the server ConfigMgr object (for schema)
        Throws:
        ScimException - for invalid filter, invalid parameters etc.

      • hasNoClientFilter

        public boolean hasNoClientFilter()
        Because ACIs can modify a request filter (tartgetFilter param), it is important to track whether client originally requested a filter as the presence of a client filter is used to determine output format per RFC7644 Sec 3.4.2.
        Returns:
        True if no filter was originally requested.

      • appendFilter

        public void appendFilter​(@NotNull
                         @NotNull Filter appendfilter)
        Takes the provided filter and adds it to an existing filter using an "and" clause. If there is no existing filter, the provided filter becomes the filter. For example for many SCIM requests, the accesscontrol system may wish to append the request with a targetFilter requirement.
        Parameters:
        appendfilter - The filter to be added to the requested filter.

      • combineFilters

        public void combineFilters​(@NotNull
                           @NotNull java.util.List<Filter> filters)
        The existing filter is combined with an and clause with a list of filters provided which are combined in an OR clause. This is done when more than one ACI is active with a targetFilter expression. E.g. ((targetFilter1 OR targetFilter2) and (requestFilter))
        Parameters:
        filters - A List of filters to be combined with OR and then appended with the original requestFilter.
